{
  "stem": "9590.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "I learned Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Hebrew was a language that I knew already when I entered the gimnazjum.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "My parents were very traditional, religious people, and they stressed very much my Hebrew education.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Being in Warkowicze, in the public school, I took lessons in Hebrew every day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And even in the summer, my mother said, to learn Hebrew, there is no vacation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "You have vacation from public school, but not from Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "In a way, maybe I resented it because some children had freedom, and they played around.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "But mother said, and I had to do it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "In the long run, I'm very thankful to her that she pressed me to do it, because I have great pleasure knowing that language.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every child that was six years old entered the public school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a mixture.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] No restrictions, whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We all attended.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And being that we were so young and naive, we didn't see the difference.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only thing that we saw there were some better students and some not so good students.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Otherwise, we all felt the same.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right, Jews and Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The gimnazjum was a strictly Jewish gimnazjum [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that was accredited from the-- the state and the country, which was a wonderful thing because going to the university, looking far ahead, if the school would not be accredited, then it would be a lot of difficulties to enter a higher learning institution.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this gave us the possibility to look in the future and work towards that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were co-ed, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The public school and the gimnazjum were co-ed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my family was religious, and we were very, very traditional.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We loved the tradition.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Saturday was observed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father went to shul, to temple.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
